{"ts": "2026-06-09T05:52:59.941983+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Unfortunately, all write operations are failing with a **403 (Resource not accessible by personal access token)** error, which means the token being used lacks write/push permissions to this repository. This is a permissions limitation I cannot fix by retrying.\n\nHere's a summary of what I've done and what needs to be implemented:\n\n---\n\n## Issue #1 Summary: \"Add authentication API docs\"\n\n### What needs to change\n\n**1. Create `docs/api/authentication.md`** — A new authentication reference page with content like:\n\n```markdown\n# Authentication\n\nThis section documents the authentication mechanisms for the API.\n\n## Overview\n\nAll API requests require authentication. The API supports the following authentication methods:\n\n### Bearer Token\n\nPass a Bearer token in the `Authorization` header of each request:\n\n    Authorization: Bearer <your-api-token>\n\n### API Key\n\nAlternatively, you may supply an API key via the `X-API-Key` header:\n\n    X-API-Key: <your-api-key>\n\n## Obtaining Credentials\n\nContact your administrator to receive an API token or key.\n\n## Error Responses\n\nIf authentication fails, the API returns a standard error response with a `401` status code. See [Errors](errors.md) for the error format.\n```\n\n**2. Update `mkdocs.yml`** — Add the authentication page to the API navigation section. The nav block should become:\n\n```yaml\nnav:\n  - Home: index.md\n  - Getting Started: getting-started.md\n  - Configuration: configuration.md\n  - API:\n      - Overview: api/overview.md\n      - Authentication: api/authentication.md\n      - Errors: api/errors.md\n```\n\n**3. Validation** — The existing `make validate` command (which runs `scripts/validate_repo.py`) checks for `site_name:` and `nav:` in `mkdocs.yml` and the presence of required files. These changes don't break any of those checks.\n\n---\n\n### Why I couldn't commit\n\nThe personal access token used for this session has **read-only** access to the repository and cannot create or update files. To apply these changes, you'll need to either:\n- Grant write access to the token, or\n- Apply the changes manually using the content above.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 518, "prompt_tokens": 8875, "total_tokens": 9393, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 53, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8384, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0006944274, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002437674, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00045066}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780984365-nkZEQlv3RvVknj131yLR", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019eaaf0-befb-7543-99d8-6f3230c6a6cf-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8875, "output_tokens": 518, "total_tokens": 9393, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8384}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 53}}}}]}}}
